arts.ttl: Race for Europe heats up with Brighton and Fulham victories
arts.sum: Brighton went up to eighth, which could become a qualifying position for the UEFA Conference League, just one point ahead of Fulham in ninth. The winners of the FA Cup qualify for the league phase of the UEFA Europa League but if they finish in the top five of the Premier League, their place will instead go to the next-highest ranked team that have not qualified for Europe via their league position.

arts.ttl: Sessegnon and Muniz on target as Fulham beat Wolves to boost European hopes
arts.sum: Wolves remain 17th in the table, five points clear of Ipswich Town having played a game more, while Fulham move up to ninth, ahead of Aston Villa on goal difference. Muniz held the ball up before finding Pereira, who in turn set up Sessegnon to score his first Premier League goal since rejoining the club in the summer.

arts.ttl: Marco Silva hopes Ryan Sessegnon gets his career back on track again at Fulham

arts.ttl: Wolves still hovering above relegation zone after home defeat to Fulham
arts.sum: Vitor Pereira’s side remain five points ahead of the bottom three but Ipswich and Leicester could cut that advantage later this week.

arts.ttl: Wolves v Fulham line-ups: No Smith Rowe, Cairney a sub, Sessegnon plays
arts.sum: Fulham are without Emile Smith Rowe at Molineux, where Tom Cairney is among the substitutes. Both players were substituted during the second half of Saturday’s 2-0 home defeat by Crystal Palace after picking up knocks. Meanwhile, Ryan Sessegnon starts in the Premier League for the first time since his return to Fulham.
